Usage: casher [options] command [arguments]
    -H, --header VALUE               add given header to HTTP requests
    -m, --check-mtime                use mtime as indicator if a file changed
    -M, --no-check-mtime             don't use mtime as indicator if a file changed
    -a, --algorithm NAME             checksum algorithm to use for detecting changes
    -A, --checksum-command CMD       command used for generating checksums
    -d, --debug                      print helpful debug output, show stacktraces
    -i, --internal                   run internal command
    -g, --enable-gc                  enable Garbage collector
    -c, --casher-dir PATH            set directory for archives and meta data
    -?, -h, --help                   display help

Available commands:
    add, checksums, extract, fetch, help, push.

Available checksum algorithms:
    crc, detect, md5, nop, sha1, sha224, sha256, sha384, sha512, tiger, whirlpool.

If set to detect, it will use tiger, md5 or crc, depending on availability.
If set to nop, files will be assumed to have changed.
